  "sentences": [
    {
      "en": "The drawing Coco found in return showed a bright yellow sun with a wide, happy smile.",
      "zh": "Coco 後來收到的那張圖畫，畫的是一個明亮的黃色太陽，帶著大大的笑臉。"
    },
    {
      "en": "It filled her with a small, wonderful kind of joy she hadn't expected.",
      "zh": "這讓她心裡湧起一種她沒想到會有的、美好的喜悅。"
    },
    {
      "en": "That evening, Coco brought the case to Mr. Pan, unsure how to even describe it.",
      "zh": "那天晚上，Coco 把這個案子告訴潘老師，不太確定該怎麼形容它。"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"There's no one to interview,\" she said. \"No name, no reason, no ending.\"",
      "zh": "她說：「沒有人可以訪問，沒有名字，沒有原因，也沒有結局。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "Mr. Pan listened, then smiled in a way Coco hadn't seen before.",
      "zh": "潘老師聽著，然後露出 Coco 之前沒見過的笑容。"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"Maybe that's the case,\" he said. \"Not everything needs a name attached to be real.\"",
      "zh": "他說：「也許這就是案子本身，不是每件事都需要一個名字才算真的。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "Bernice thought about that for a moment. \"But a podcast needs something to say.\"",
      "zh": "Bernice 想了一下：「但 podcast 得說點什麼吧。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"Then say that,\" Mr. Pan said. \"Say that kindness doesn't always have an owner.\"",
      "zh": "潘老師說：「那就說這個，說善意不一定有一個主人。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "Coco wrote the sentence down right away, before she could forget the exact words.",
      "zh": "Coco 馬上把這句話寫下來，怕自己忘記確切的用字。"
    },
    {
      "en": "That night, before going home, Coco stopped by Locker 113 one more time.",
      "zh": "那天晚上，回家前，Coco 又順路去了一趟113號置物櫃。"
    },
    {
      "en": "She had brought something small from her own bag: a short note with three words on it.",
      "zh": "她從自己的書包裡帶了一樣小東西：一張只有三個字的短紙條。"
    },
    {
      "en": "She didn't tell Bernice what she wrote. She just placed it inside and closed the door.",
      "zh": "她沒有告訴 Bernice 她寫了什麼，她只是把紙條放進去，關上門。"
    },
    {
      "en": "The next morning, the note was gone, and something new sat in its place: a small drawing of a smiling sun.",
      "zh": "隔天早上，那張紙條不見了，取而代之的是一樣新東西：一張畫著笑臉太陽的小圖畫。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Coco realized she would probably never know who took her note, or who left the drawing.",
      "zh": "Coco 意識到她大概永遠不會知道是誰拿走了她的紙條，或是誰留下了那張圖畫。"
    },
    {
      "en": "For once, that felt completely fine.",
      "zh": "這一次，這樣的感覺完全沒問題。"
    },
    {
      "en": "The episode about Locker 113 was short, only a few minutes long.",
      "zh": "關於113號置物櫃的這一集很短，只有幾分鐘。"
    },
    {
      "en": "It ended with one line from Coco: \"We didn't find who started this. We're not sure anyone remembers anymore. But it's still going.\"",
      "zh": "結尾是 Coco 說的一句話：「我們沒找到是誰開始的，也許連他們自己都不記得了，但它現在還在繼續。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "After the episode aired, three more lockers around the school quietly started the same habit.",
      "zh": "這一集播出後，學校裡又有三個置物櫃悄悄開始了一樣的習慣。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Bernice kept a private list of which lockers, just for herself, and never told anyone the number.",
      "zh": "Bernice 自己私下記了一份清單，寫下是哪幾個置物櫃，但沒有告訴任何人號碼。"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"Some things,\" she told Coco, \"work better if nobody's counting too closely.\"",
      "zh": "她告訴 Coco：「有些事情，如果沒有人盯得太緊，反而做得更好。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "Case six ended without a single name, and somehow, it was one of their favorite episodes yet.",
      "zh": "案件六在沒有出現任何一個名字的情況下結束了，不知怎麼地，這卻成了他們目前最喜歡的一集。"
    },
    {
      "en": "That weekend, a new note appeared in the Friday Box — but this one made both of them laugh before they even finished reading it.",
      "zh": "那個週末，Friday Box 裡出現了一張新紙條——但這張紙條他們還沒讀完就已經笑了出來。"
    },
    {
      "en": "It read: \"The guard's dog barks at exactly 3:33 every afternoon, at nothing. Please investigate. This is very important.\"",
      "zh": "上面寫著：「警衛的狗每天下午三點三十三分準時對著空氣狂吠，請調查，這件事非常重要。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"Finally,\" Bernice said, \"a case that isn't going to make me cry.\"",
      "zh": "Bernice 說：「終於，一個不會讓我哭的案子。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "That same week, the school held its yearly sports day, with a baseball game in the morning and a basketball match after lunch.",
      "zh": "同一個星期，學校辦了年度運動會，早上是棒球比賽，午餐後是籃球比賽。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Every student had to wear the school uniform, though some added a T-shirt underneath for extra warmth.",
      "zh": "每個學生都得穿學校制服，不過有些人裡面多加了一件 T 恤保暖。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Bernice, who wore shorts and old sneakers, said tennis was more fun than any team sport.",
      "zh": "Bernice 穿著短褲和舊球鞋，說網球比任何團體運動都好玩。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Coco preferred to sit and watch, holding a cool drink and cheering for her team from a safe distance.",
      "zh": "Coco 比較喜歡坐著看，手裡拿著一杯冰涼的飲料，在安全距離外幫自己的隊伍加油。"
    },
    {
      "en": "After the games, the school store sold small prizes: a kite, a drum-shaped keychain, a tiny robot toy, and a box of colored paint.",
      "zh": "比賽結束後，學校商店賣起小獎品：一個風箏、鼓形鑰匙圈、一個小機器人玩具，還有一盒彩色顏料。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Mei won a ticket for a free lemon pie at the food stand, and she shared it with Coco and Bernice.",
      "zh": "Mei 贏得一張免費檸檬派的兌換券，她跟 Coco 和 Bernice 一起分享。"
    },
    {
      "en": "The stand also sold sweet potato snacks, salad in small cups, and honey tea in paper bottles.",
      "zh": "攤位還賣了地瓜點心、小杯沙拉，還有裝在紙瓶裡的蜂蜜茶。"
    },
    {
      "en": "A local shop offered a small prize to anyone who could throw a ball through a paper ring from ten steps away.",
      "zh": "有一間當地商店提供小獎品，只要能從十步外把球丟過一個紙圈，就能得獎。"
    },
    {
      "en": "In PE class, they had to complete a small obstacle course: bow under a rope, catch a ball, and cover a short distance without stopping.",
      "zh": "體育課裡，他們得完成一個小小的障礙賽：低頭鑽過繩子、接住一顆球，還要不停下來跑過一小段距離。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Bernice managed the whole course in under a minute, while Coco stopped twice to fix her shoe.",
      "zh": "Bernice 不到一分鐘就完成整個障礙賽，Coco 卻停了兩次綁鞋帶。"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"I'd rather lose slowly than fall and hurt myself,\" Coco said, only half joking.",
      "zh": "Coco 半開玩笑地說：「我寧願慢慢輸，也不要跌倒受傷。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "Bernice's room, everyone agreed, was famously messy: a couch buried under clothes, a lamp with no bulb, and a drawer she refused to open.",
      "zh": "大家都公認 Bernice 的房間很出名地亂：沙發被衣服埋住，一盞沒燈泡的檯燈，還有一個她死都不肯打開的抽屜。"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"It's not dirty,\" she insisted, \"it's just... a system nobody else understands.\"",
      "zh": "她堅持說：「這不算髒，只是⋯⋯一套別人看不懂的整理方式。」"
    }
